draw(P--R);
draw(R--SS);
draw(rightanglemark(Q,P,R,3.5));
draw(rightanglemark(R,SS,P,3.5));
[/asy]

Then by the angle addition formula,
\begin{align*}
\sin (\angle RPQ + \angle QPS) &= \sin \angle RPQ \cos \angle QPS + \cos \angle RPQ \sin \angle QPS \\
&= \frac{7}{25} \cos \angle QPS + \sqrt{1 - \frac{49}{625}} \sin \angle QPS \\
&= \frac{7}{25} \cos \angle QPS + \frac{24}{25} \sin \angle QPS.
\end{align*}Since $\triangle QPS$ is a right triangle, $\sin \angle QPS = \frac{5}{25} = \frac{1}{5}$ and $\cos \angle QPS = \frac{24}{25},$ so
\[\sin \angle RPS = \frac{7}{25} \cdot \frac{24}{25} + \sqrt{1 - \frac{49}{625}} \cdot \frac{1}{5} = \boxed{\frac{47}{125}}.\]

